Title : Noeick River
Text : The '''Noeick River''' is a [[river]] in the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast region]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], flowing west out of the northernmost [[Pacific Ranges]] to enter saltwater on the east side of [[South Bentinck Arm]], immediately to the north of the mouth of the [[Taleomey River]] at Taleomey Narrows.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/16970.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Noeick River"]</ref>  

The locality of [[South Bentinck]] is located at the river's mouth.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/40872.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "South Bentinck (locality)"]</ref>  There was a [[List of Nuxalk villages|Nuxalk village]], ''Nuiku'', on a raised mound south of the mouth of the Noieck River.  Another village, ''Kadis'', was on the east side of South Bentinck Arm about Â¼-mile north of the mouth of the Noieck.<ref>[http://www.canadiangenealogy.net/indians/bellacoola_indians.htm ''The Indian Tribes of North America'', John Swanton, 1953, quoted in canadiangeneaology.net website]</ref>

The river originates at the [[Noeick Glacier]], which is to the northwest of [[Mount Jacobsen]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/16968.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Noeick Glacier"]</ref>

